# Cima Project Conventions

## Naming Conventions
- **Classes and React Components**: \`PascalCase\` (e.g., \`class UserProfile\`, \`function MovieDetails()\`)
- **Variables and Functions**: \`camelCase\` (e.g., \`const userData\`, \`function fetchMovies()\`)
- **File Names**: \`kebab-case\` for ALL files including components (e.g., \`user-auth-service.js\`, \`movie-details.jsx\`, \`auth-controller.js\`)

## Git Branch & Commit Format
When working on tasks, please ensure you use the following exact formats.

### Branches
Format: \`type/SCRUM-ID-short-description\`
- **type**: \`feature\`, \`fix\`, \`hotfix\`, \`chore\`, or \`refactor\`
- **SCRUM-ID**: The specific Jira/Scrum board ticket ID (e.g., \`SCRUM-42\`)
- **short-description**: A deeply hyphenated brief explanation

**Example**: \`feature/SCRUM-42-filter-movies-genre\`

### Commits
Format: \`[SCRUM-ID] Brief description of changes\`
- Every commit message must begin with exactly the bracketed Scrum ID.

**Example**: \`[SCRUM-42] add movie filtering by genre and fetch genres list natively\`
